cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper is about a framework for annotating text data using an active-learning based assistance system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The use of active learning and pre-annotations suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on improving annotator efficiency could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
